Sec. 147.027. COMMISSION MERCHANT'S COPY OF BOND. As soon as
practicable after the recording of a bond, a commission merchant
shall request, and the county clerk shall provide, a certified copy
of the bond. The commission merchant shall post that copy in a
conspicuous place in the main office of the commission merchant's
principal place of business.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1381, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

